making a choice without meaning to
Some choices in life are made with determination, "I'm going to do this! and some choices are not.
If the former is a "willful choice," then the latter can be said to be a "non-decisive choice.

Often, choices that are not made with the best of intentions have a profound impact on the rest of one's life.

Choices that are made with the best of intentions create a bias that wants to think they were the right ones.
[Justification of past choices].
